<br>
I simply start with a nuke and then run with my TBoots.  Using my Staff of Temperate Flux, I gauge the distance until I see a full screen of Out of Range messages.<br>
<br>
I then stop, pause a second, and nuke without turning around.  I then start running again. Sometimes, I get hit, but that's not a big issue. <br>
<br>
Just and FYI.  Not snaring saves on mana for single kites.  I can fit in two this way instead of one at level 36. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udracomin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dracomin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/01 11:28:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Latest The Overthere Strategy</span><hr size=1> For those who play light races, you need to be on the lookout for the General and his goons.  <br>
<br>
I died a number of times due to them, but I eventually wised up.  Between about 2 AM and noon, stay east of pos 700.  This is a fair distance east of FM ledge.  Some goons will go just a bit east of FM ledge, but not far past it.  Just stay east of pos 700 to make sure.  If you have to go to the ledge, try to delay it after noon.  Goons are usually seen around FM ledge between 3 am and 7 am, but I have seen them there as late as 11 am.<br>
 <p>Dracomin Spidernooker<BR>
Level 55 Wizard<BR>
<BR>
Spooch<BR>
Level 19 Cleric<BR>


</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaraton.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Araton</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 4:03:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Latest The Overthere Strategy</span><hr size=1> I am now saving up for tboots so i can start soloing. i am level 39. Would the overthere be a good place to hunt at my level? <br>
<br>
-Araton <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspankda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spankda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 5:34:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Goons and The Overthere</span><hr size=1> Okay.  I'm amiable to Venril Sathir now and started only apprehensive, so the Dragoons were never a problem. My first experience with the Dragoons was when they wiped out half of my group near the ledge.  I then joined another group and they wiped out half of that group.<br>
<br>
In short, there are a lot of stupid people grouping near the ledge (entrance to FM zone area) that get killed multiple times by the Dragoons.  If you hear, see, smell, taste, or feel a Dragoon nearby and you're KoS to them.  Run!  Do not stop.  Do not ask questions.  Run.  They are fast-as-SoW and hit hard.<br>
<br>
Now, they have a very set schedule.  I can tell you that at 11pm game time each night, the Dragoons march out of their little building in file and go on a hunt across the Western side of the zone.  I know this because I sit at the entrance to the Outpost and watch them march past me every night, 11pm game-time.  <br>
<br>
The Dragoons stay out until approximately 5am game time, depending on how hunting goes.  If lots of PC's are drawing them back to the FM zone and such, then they're out longer.<br>
<br>
On hunting this zone at 39.  Yes, 39 is good.  I believe up through 46 will be good in this zone, but I'm not 100% positive.  If you are KoS to Venril Sathir, you should consider killing the Scorpikis because they drop the coin that all the bards need for their Nostrolo drums.  In short, get coins and sell them to bards.  Every night, I see bards asking about the coin and *no one* hunts the Scorpikis.<br>
<br>
I am amiable to most Scorpikis, so I don't hunt them.<br>
<br>
I have successfully tri-kited three Sarnak Berzerkers there.  Typically, I'll grab something, snare and nuke it, then just non-snare kite the other.  Depending on my mood.  I get tired of running.<br>
<br>
The Kunark Rhinos run at SoW to the equivalent of their level.  So, you're gonna have a level 37 SoW'd Rhino killing you if you have JBoots or TBoots and are being chased by a Rhino that is not snared.  In short, if you agro an unsnared Rhino and you don't have a 40+ SoW, you are dead.<br>
<br>
The Tigers are fast, but not as fast as the Rhinos.  I can not *gain* distance on a Tiger.  Hence, I don't hunt Tigers.  The two critters I avoid are Tigers and Rhinos.  Both have a *very* short agro radius.  I have agro'd them only by accident in the past.<br>
<br>
Being amiable to Venril Sathir means I have a 100% safe place to meditate.  I go AFK for extended periods while med'ing.  I then cast my TBoots, snare, nuke, and gate back to the Outpost to med for a while.  Of course, if I'm not careful at night, the Dragoons take my kills.<br>
<br>
At about 40, I am going to run from The Overthere to the Emerald Jungle and attempt to kite on the ledge near the zone to the Field of Bone.  I will report on my success there.  I do know that the Tottering Gorillas, which are Undead and hence see through invisiblity, are faster than SoW. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxendapus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xendapus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 5:50:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Goons and The Overthere</span><hr size=1> Most gnomes are non KOS in the overthere.<br>
<br>
Bonds of force is nice, i just got it <br>
<br>
Wish I could afford T-boots, or even find them which damn vendor is it?<br>
<br>
I am not even considering trying for J-boots lol.<br>
